         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">EXAMINATION FOR THE DEGREES OF BACHELOR OF MEDICINE AND DOCTOR OF MEDICINE UNDER THE SPECIAL REGULATIONS. ¶ MEDICAL BOTANY, MATERIA MEDICA, THERAPEUTICS, AND WRITING PRESCRIPTIONS WITHOUT ABBREVIATION...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.02.00a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Examination Paper, University of Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Univeristy of Melbourne calendar, 1863-1864</seg>
                     <seg style="">, pp. ccv-ccvi. The examinations were held in February Term.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>EXAMINATION FOR THE DEGREES OF BACHELOR OF MEDICINE AND DOCTOR OF MEDICINE UNDER THE SPECIAL REGULATIONS.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">MEDICAL BOTANY, MATERIA MEDICA, THERAPEUTICS, AND WRITING PRESCRIPTIONS WITHOUT ABBREVIATIONS.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">(<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Richard Eades, A.M. and M.B., and Ferdinand F. Mueller, M.D. and Ph.D.</seg>)</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I. —1. What are the distincive characters of the natural order of <name key="Cucurbitaceae">Cucurbitaceae</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">2. Enumerate the principal medicinal plants of the order of <name key="Labiatae">Labiatae</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">3. Describe the differences of the stems of dicotyledonous, monocotyledonous, and acotyledonous plants.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">4. What is the botanical name of the plant yielding the Calumbo root, what its native country, its prominent medicinal principle and therapeutic value.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">5. Explain the distinctive characters of <name key="Convolvulaceae">Convolvulaceae</name>, and enumerate the principal medicinal plants of the order.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">II. —1. Describe the characteristic action on the system of opium, aconite, and belladonna.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">2. Describe the symptoms of an overdose of hydrocyanic acid, which would cause death in, say, from twenty to thirty minutes.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">3. What are the principal foetid gum resins? Describe their action on the system.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">4. Describe the difference in the physiological action of potash and chalybeates.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">5. What are the simple bitter tonics, the astringent tonics, and the aromatic tonics?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">PRESCRIPTION.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Write in Latin without contractions a purgative medicine, and an antiphlogistic mixture in the first stage of pleuritis.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Convolvulaceae">Convolvulaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cucurbitaceae">Cucurbitaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Labiatae">Labiatae</name>
            </p>
